quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,109,"So do not be in doubt ňĻO Prophetňļ about what those ňĻpagansňļ worship. They worship nothing except what their forefathers worshipped before ňĻthemňļ. And We will certainly give them their share ňĻof punishmentňļ in full, without any reduction"
  11,110,"Indeed, We had given Moses the Scripture, but differences arose regarding it. Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled ňĻat onceňļ. They are truly in alarming doubt about it"
  11,111,And surely your Lord will fully pay all for their deeds. He is certainly All-Aware of what they do
  11,112,"So be steadfast as you are commanded ňĻO Prophetňļ, along with those who turn ňĻin submission to Godňļ with you. And do not transgress. Surely He is All-Seeing of what you ňĻbelieversňļ do"
  11,113,"And do not be inclined to the wrongdoers or you will be touched by the Fire. For then you would have no protectors other than God, nor would you be helped"
  11,114,Establish prayer ňĻO Prophetňļ at both ends of the day and in the early part of the night.¬†Surely good deeds wipe out evil deeds. That is a reminder for the mindful
  11,115,And be patient! Certainly God does not discount the reward of the good-doers
  11,116,"If only there had been among the ňĻdestroyedňļ peoples before you, ňĻO believers,ňļ virtuous individuals who forbade corruption in the land‚ÄĒother than the few We had saved ňĻfrom the tormentňļ. But the wrongdoers ňĻonlyňļ pursued their ňĻworldlyňļ pleasures, becoming wicked"
  11,117,And your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ would never destroy a society unjustly while its people were acting rightly
